📊 Dataset Link :-----
>https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mehmettahiraslan/customer-shopping-dataset


🔍 Objective:-----

The goal of this project was to dive deep into a retail sales dataset and uncover patterns, trends, and insights to help the retail business make informed decisions.



🛠️ Tools Used:-----

 Power BI , Excel , MySql



Key Aspects of the Project:-----



1. Data Loading and Cleaning:

> Ensured the dataset was clean and ready for analysis.

2. Descriptive Statistics: 

> Calculated key statistics such as mean, median, mode, and standard deviation.

3. Time Series Analysis: 

> Analyzed sales trends over time to identify seasonal patterns and anomalies.

4. Customer and Product Analysis: 

> Investigated customer demographics and purchasing behavior.

5. Visualization: 

>Used bar charts, line plots, and heatmaps to present insights visually.

6. Recommendations: 

> Provided actionable recommendations based on the EDA findings.





Learning Objectives Achieved:-----



> Gained hands-on experience in data cleaning and exploratory data analysis.

Developed skills in interpreting descriptive statistics and time series analysis.

Enhanced my ability to use data visualization for effective communication of insights.



Insights & Recommendations:-----



1. Sales Trends: 

> Identified peak sales periods and seasonal trends, suggesting targeted marketing campaigns during high-sales months.

2. Customer Demographics: 

> Discovered key customer segments, enabling personalized marketing strategies.

3. Performance: 

> Highlighted top-performing products, recommending stock adjustments and promotional activities.



I am immensely grateful to Oasis Infobyte for this opportunity. This project has not only strengthened my analytical skills but also my proficiency in Power BI. Looking forward to the next challenge!

Feel free to connect with me to discuss data analytics, Power BI, or any exciting opportunities! 🌟



